latestIgtvVideos.title: Paathshala
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here’s to all the children and to everyone’s inner child. This year has been trying, exhausting, and lonely. As We looked at the new normal for school going children, sitting in front of a laptop, missing their friends, and growing up disconnected from their second home, school, We wondered what it would be like having to grow and learn through the digital fatigue. In this piece, @mayuri30 wanted the dancers to exude the energy of a classroom, one with pranks and chaos and joy and play. We wish for the energy of the real normal to never be forgotten.

Choreography - @mayuri30

latestIgtvVideos.title: Just Dance - let the rhythm get you
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Just Dance - let the rhythm get you.

Dhol - The Percussion Discussion

The Dhol is a drum used extensively in North Indian folk music, festivities, and celebrations. It’s simple rhythm makes it accessible to everyone. The movements it defines are athletic, speedy, and celebratory. Inspired by the folk feel of the dhol, the choreography is fun, interactive, and will leave you tapping your feet.

latestPosts.caption:
Sometimes, in all our lives, comes a connection so profound that makes all of our sufferings and rock bottoms worth it. All the bends and turns, getting lost on our paths and mistakes made, and all the coincidences suddenly feel like divine interventions to get us to our true home.  Chitralekha and Holm, we were privileged to witness this journey of yours. If we could dedicate an anthem to you, it would be “God blessed the broken roads that led me straight to you”. 

We, at HOTC, raise our toast to the love and respect that you have found in each other. May everyone be blessed with a love so profound that makes every battle worth it.
